                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_aqazzag" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>aqazzag</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>aǧazzag</orth><form type="variant"><orth>aǧajzag</orth></form></form><sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>отменный</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>excellent</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>хороший</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>good</q></tr></sense></sense><sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>как следует</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>as it should be</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>основательно</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>thoroughly</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>хорошенько</q></tr></sense></sense><exampleGrp><example><quote>x˳ycaw taǧd næ kæny, fælæ k˳y cævy, wæd aqazzag</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>бог не спешит, но уж если ударит, то основательно</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>God is in no hurry, but if he hits, he does it thoroughly</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Čerm."/><biblScope>175</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>walynmæ kʼævda aqazzag nyzǧælsta</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>тем временем дождь полил вовсю</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>meanwhile the rain started pouring down</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_FS"/><biblScope>1957 VI 36</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>axæstony, dam, Dawita aqazzag nal ū, mæly, dam</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>в тюрьме, говорят, Дауита в неважном состоянии, умирает, говорят</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>they say Dauita is in poor condition in prison, she is dying, they say</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>61</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>aǧazzag lodærtæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>отменные лодыри</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>excellent idlers</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_SD"/><biblScope>295%l3%l</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>tillægbæl toxi aǧazzagi bænttæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>решающие дни борьбы за урожай</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>decisive days of the struggle for the harvest</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_SD"/><biblScope>176%l1%l</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>bæxti ænaǧazzag kænuncæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>лошадей приводят в негодность</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>horses are worn out</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_SD"/><biblScope>161%l4%l</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>Ʒаххоbæl aǧaziaw %i(sic!)%i wæzzaw bonttæ iskodta</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>для Дзаххо настали чрезвычайно тяжелые дни</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>extremely difficult days have come for Dzahho</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Bes._Ka_ke"/><biblScope>38</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>sīftyǧta jæ aǧajzag, fexsta fīdaryl</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>зарядил ее (пушку) хорошенько, выстрелил в крепость</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>he loaded it (the gun) well and shot at the fortress</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>I 39</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><exampleGrp><example><quote>x˳ycaw taǧd næ kæny, fælæ k˳y cævy, wæd aqazzag</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>бог не спешит, но уж если ударит, то основательно</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>God is in no hurry, but if he hits, he does it thoroughly</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Čerm."/><biblScope>175</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>walynmæ kʼævda aqazzag nyzǧælsta</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>тем временем дождь полил вовсю</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>meanwhile the rain started pouring down</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_FS"/><biblScope>1957 VI 36</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>axæstony, dam, Dawita aqazzag nal ū, mæly, dam</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>в тюрьме, говорят, Дауита в неважном состоянии, умирает, говорят</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>they say Dauita is in poor condition in prison, she is dying, they say</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>61</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>aǧazzag lodærtæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>отменные лодыри</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>excellent idlers</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_SD"/><biblScope>295%l3%l</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>tillægbæl toxi aǧazzagi bænttæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>решающие дни борьбы за урожай</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>decisive days of the struggle for the harvest</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_SD"/><biblScope>176%l1%l</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>bæxti ænaǧazzag kænuncæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>лошадей приводят в негодность</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>horses are worn out</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_SD"/><biblScope>161%l4%l</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>Ʒаххоbæl aǧaziaw %i(sic!)%i wæzzaw bonttæ iskodta</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>для Дзаххо настали чрезвычайно тяжелые дни</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>extremely difficult days have come for Dzahho</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Bes._Ka_ke"/><biblScope>38</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>sīftyǧta jæ aǧajzag, fexsta fīdaryl</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>зарядил ее (пушку) хорошенько, выстрелил в крепость</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>he loaded it (the gun) well and shot at the fortress</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>I 39</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Из <ref type="xr" target="#entry_aqaz"/> | %iaǧaz%i ‘помощь’, ‘польза’ и адъективного суффикса %i-ag%i, с появлением %ij%i перед %iz%i в дигорском и закономерным удвоением %iz%i в иронском (ср. и. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bazzajyn"/> — д. %ibajzajun%i ‘остаться’). На движение значения ‘помощь’ → ‘отменный’ повлияла, возможно, контаминация с другим %bарабским%b словом <mentioned xml:lang="ar"><lang/> <w>aḫaṣṣ</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (ﺍﺨﺺ)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (ﺍﺨﺺ)</note> <gloss><q>специальный</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ar"><w/> <gloss><q>отменный</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ar"><w/> <gloss><q>исключительный</q></gloss></mentioned>, .</etym><etym xml:lang="en">From <ref type="xr" target="#entry_aqaz"/> | %iaǧaz%i ‘help’, ‘benefit’ and the adjectivizer %i-ag%i, with the appearance of %ij%i before %iz%i in Digor and the regular doubling of %iz%i in Iron (cf. Iron <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bazzajyn"/> — Digor %ibajzajun%i ‘stay’). Perhaps contamination with the %bArabic%b word <mentioned xml:lang="ar"><lang/> <w>aḫaṣṣ</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (ﺍﺨﺺ)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (ﺍﺨﺺ)</note> <gloss><q>special</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ar"><w/> <gloss><q>excellent</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ar"><w/> <gloss><q>exclusive</q></gloss></mentioned>,  influenced the shift of the meaning ‘help’ → ‘excellent’.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>